Description: Fragment of handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 181, 45. Name Andrikos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0316.15.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1045)
